16/01/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police arrested four alleged members of an organised crime group during two raids in Sarajevo's elite Ciglane neighbourhood. 
On Monday (January 14th), police detained alleged gang leader Muhamed Ali Gasi and two other members. 
On Tuesday, police arrested Gasi's brother, Aziz. 
About ten days ago police arrested five other alleged members of the group. 
Another is being sought. 
The gang, believed to be one of the largest in BiH, has been implicated in murders, blackmail and racketeering. 
(Dnevni Avaz - 16/01/08; Fena, RTRS -15/01/08)
